#: ../../D/deserves-to-lose.rst:5
msgid "deserves to lose"
msgstr "deserves to lose"

#: ../../D/deserves-to-lose.rst:7
msgid "adj\\."
msgstr "形容詞"

#: ../../D/deserves-to-lose.rst:9
msgid ""
"[common] Said of someone who willfully does the :ref:`Wrong-Thing`\\; "
"humorously, if one uses a feature known to be :ref:`marginal`\\. What is "
"meant is that one deserves the consequences of one's :ref:`losing` actions. "
"\"Boy, anyone who tries to use :ref:`mess-dos` deserves to :ref:`lose`\\!\" "
"( :ref:`ITS` fans used to say the same thing of :ref:`Unix`\\; many still "
"do.) See also :ref:`screw`\\, :ref:`chomp`\\, :ref:`bagbiter`\\."
msgstr ""
"[一般的] わざと\\ :ref:`Wrong-Thing`\\ をする人について言う。ユーモラスに、\\ :ref:`marginal`\\ "
"だと知られている機能を使う場合にも。意味するところは、自分の\\ :ref:`losing`\\ "
"な行為の結果を受けて当然だ、ということである。「まったく、\\ :ref:`mess-dos`\\ を使おうなんてやつは\\ :ref:`lose`\\"
" して当然だ!」(\\ :ref:`ITS`\\ のファンはかつて\\ :ref:`Unix`\\ "
"について同じことを言ったものだ。今でも多くがそう言う。)\\ :ref:`screw`\\ 、\\ :ref:`chomp`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`bagbiter`\\ も参照。"
